headline.main: U.S. Factory Orders Rise for Second Straight Month
headline.print_headline: U.S. Factory Orders Rise for Second Straight Month

lead_paragraph: New orders for U.S.-made goods increased for a second straight month in January, suggesting the recovery of the manufacturing sector was gaining momentum as rising prices for commodities spur demand for machinery.
